---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import PageHero from "../../components/page/PageHero.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Copyright | Virtual Ventures"
  description="Copyright notes for Virtual Ventures patterns, photos, artwork, PDFs, QR codes and original content."
  showFooterBreadcrumbs={false}
>
  <PageHero
    eyebrow="Original Work"
    title="Copyright"
    description="A clear note about sharing links, respecting original work, and keeping Virtual Ventures patterns traceable to the official source."
  />

  <main class="page-shell">
    <section class="page-intro">
      <p class="eyebrow">Copyright</p>
      <h1>Free to use, not free to copy</h1>
      <p>
        Virtual Ventures patterns, photos, artwork, layouts, files, videos and
        written content are original workshop materials unless stated otherwise.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section content-left">
      <article class="content-card">
        <h2>What belongs to Virtual Ventures</h2>
        <p>
          The original crochet pattern text, stitch notes, pattern photos,
          finished item photos, product photos, printable PDF files, blog posts,
          page layouts, QR code destinations, pattern IDs and workshop wording
          belong to Virtual Ventures unless a page clearly says otherwise.
        </p>
        <p>
          Free website patterns are still copyrighted. They are shared so people
          can learn, make and enjoy the craft, not so the pattern text or files
          can be copied into other listings, downloads, databases or courses.
        </p>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section content-right">
      <article class="content-card">
        <h2>You may</h2>
        <p>
          You may link to Virtual Ventures pages, save the official page for
          your own use, make items from the patterns for yourself, and share the
          original website link with friends, groups, students or customers.
        </p>
        <p>
          You may also use short quotes when discussing or reviewing a pattern,
          as long as you clearly credit Virtual Ventures and link to the original
          page.
        </p>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section content-left">
      <article class="content-card">
        <h2>You may not</h2>
        <p>
          Please do not copy, repost, upload, resell, translate, redistribute or
          repackage Virtual Ventures pattern text, photos, PDFs, charts, images
          or downloads as your own product or resource.
        </p>
        <p>
          Please do not turn the patterns into another download, video, course,
          kit, bundle, database, scraper dataset, AI training dataset or
          marketplace listing without written permission.
        </p>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section content-right">
      <article class="content-card">
        <h2>Watermarks, IDs and QR codes</h2>
        <p>
          Patterns may include copyright footers, watermarks, QR codes, version
          numbers, pattern IDs and verification links. These are there to help
          people find the official source, updates, corrections, stitch help and
          safety notes.
        </p>
        <p>
          Please do not remove or hide those details from Virtual Ventures files
          or images.
        </p>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section content-left">
      <article class="content-card">
        <h2>Optional support copies</h2>
        <p>
          Some patterns may be free to read on the website and also available as
          an optional paid printable PDF on Etsy. Future KDP books may collect a
          year of free monthly patterns into one printed book.
        </p>
        <p>
          These support copies help Virtual Ventures keep making free patterns,
          tutorials and livestreams. They are optional, and buying one does not
          give permission to redistribute the file or printed content.
        </p>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section content-right">
      <article class="content-card">
        <h2>Report a suspicious copy</h2>
        <p>
          If you find a pattern, photo, PDF, QR code or listing that looks like a
          stolen or confusing copy of Virtual Ventures work, please report it.
          Useful details include the link, screenshots, seller name, platform,
          date found and why it looks suspicious.
        </p>
        <p>
          Reporting page: <a href="/report-stolen-pattern/">Report a Copy</a>.
          Contact email placeholder: [contact email].
        </p>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="content-closing-card">
      <p>
        The kindest way to share a free Virtual Ventures pattern is to share the
        official link, not a copied file.
      </p>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>
